# Security Rules

## Environment Variables

### Two categories — never mix them

| Type | Prefix | Visible in browser? | Where to use |
|---|---|---|---|
| Secret | _(no prefix)_ | ❌ NO | `src/lib/api/` only |
| Public | `NEXT_PUBLIC_` | ✅ YES | Anywhere |

```bash
# .env.local — NEVER commit this file
SMTP_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
SMTP_PORT=587
CONTACT_EMAIL_API_KEY=sk-live-xxxxx
DB_CONNECTION_STRING=postgresql://...

# Safe to use in components
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://smartinfra.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
```

```js
// ✅ Secret env var — only in lib/api/ or app/api/
// src/lib/api/contact.js
import 'server-only'
const apiKey = process.env.CONTACT_EMAIL_API_KEY  // ✅ server-only file

// ❌ NEVER in a component or "use client" file
"use client"
const apiKey = process.env.CONTACT_EMAIL_API_KEY  // ❌ undefined in browser, but exposes intent
```

---

## `server-only` Package

Every file in `src/lib/api/` MUST have this as the first line:

```js
import 'server-only'
```

This causes an intentional **build error** if a Client Component tries to import the file. It is a hard guardrail — never remove it.

---

## `.env.example` — Always Keep Updated

`.env.example` is committed to git. It documents required variables with empty values:

```bash
# .env.example — commit this
CONTACT_EMAIL_API_KEY=
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=
DB_CONNECTION_STRING=

NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=
```

`.env.local` is NEVER committed. Verify `.gitignore` contains:
```
.env.local
.env*.local
```

